# See https://help.github.com/articles/ignoring-files/ for more about ignoring files.

# dependencies
/node_modules
/.pnp
.pnp.*
.yarn/*
!.yarn/patches
!.yarn/plugins
!.yarn/releases
!.yarn/versions

# testing
/coverage

# next.js
/.next/
/out/

# production
/build

# misc
.DS_Store
*.pem

# debug
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
.pnpm-debug.log*

# env files (can opt-in for committing if needed)
.env*

# vercel
.vercel

# typescript
*.tsbuildinfo
next-env.d.ts

# optional persisted auto-translations (see I18N_PERSIST_TRANSLATIONS)
/lib/i18n/generated/*.json

# PHASE 8.11R — narrow, repo-root-anchored guard against the specific
# accidental Tesseract OCR artifact previously observed being written to the
# repository root before lib/vaylo/smart-talk/ocr/tesseract-runtime-policy.ts
# started supplying an explicit OS-temp-directory-based cachePath. Deliberately
# root-anchored (not a global "eng.traineddata" pattern) and deliberately
# does NOT ignore "*.traineddata" broadly, so any future intentionally
# committed/versioned OCR language asset is unaffected without an explicit
# policy decision. No system-temp-directory or absolute/Windows-specific
# path is added here — the real cache directory lives entirely outside the
# repository.
/eng.traineddata
*.traineddata.tmp
